    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-10-15T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-10-15T06:00:00-05:00" n="88"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d88">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2190</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-15T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 15, 1915, noon</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 12.40. p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>412. Reports come to Servian Legation that Bulgaria has attacked Servia in rear
                    without declaring war and situation perilous. Press declared yesterday Italy
                    decided not to send troops Saloniki but rumor persists that aid will be sent
                    Servia possibly through Albania.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
